Text:
@hackster117 since you didn't quote the whole error message, I can only guess 2 possible reasons: 

1)Your downloaded file might be corrupted (deleting the data and re-downloading it should fix it)
2)This is actually weird but happened to me more than once, so not to count this one out; if the file name consists of quite a few characters (i.e. it has a huge filename) it might exceed the permitted character use for naming a folder in your os, thus won't letting you extract it. You should be able to change the soon-to-be-extracted folder name to a shorter one to get around it.
